            "question": {
                "text": "Consider a CPU where all the instructions require 7 \nclock cycles to complete execution. There are 140 \ninstructions in the instruction set. It is found that 125 \ncontrol signals are needed to be generated by the \ncontrol unit. While designing the horizontal micro-\nprogrammed control unit, single address field format \nis used for branch control logic. What is the \nminimum size of the control word and control \naddress register?",
                "images": [
                    "assets/Computer Organization and Architecture/COA_ALU_and_Control_Unit_P17_X2055.png"
                ],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "125, 7",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "125, 10",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "135, 9",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "135, 10 \n\nRISC and CISC",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "D"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "Total number of instructions = 140 \n\nEach intruction requires = 7 cycle \n\nTotal number of micro operations = 140 \\times 7  \n\n= 980  instn | operations|cw \n\nControl memory =980 CW \n\nNIA|A.F|CAR = [log10 980] \n\nCAR\n10 bit\n=\n\n\nHorizontal  program \n\n125 CS = 125 bits required \n\n\n\n125 + 10 = 135 \n\nCW = 135 \n\nCAR = 10 bit",
                "images": [
                    "assets/Computer Organization and Architecture/COA_ALU_and_Control_Unit_P20_X2296.png"
                ],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
